                            <comment id="12906838" author="tboehme" created="Tue, 7 Sep 2010 15:36:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch for reported bug which &apos;unsignes&apos; the return value&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027194" author="lars t" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2011 21:17:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;RandomAccessBuffer usage was introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-948&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t use temporty files by default for all PDF sizes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-948&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-948&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Hopefully switching the default to in-memory scratch buffers in 1.5.0 doesn&apos;t raised a problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027460" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 1 May 2011 14:07:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the patch in revision 1098307 as proposed by Timo Boehme.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution to Timo and thanks to Lars for the pointer!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027465" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 1 May 2011 15:17:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In revision 1098350 I fixed an issue introduced in the last revision.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Kevin Jackson for the hint!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027472" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 1 May 2011 17:05:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had to replace the Arrays.copyOf(byte[], int) call in revision 1098368 to ensure java 1.5 compliance&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13027473" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 1 May 2011 17:09:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wether it is to warm or to late. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; My last commit introduced an ArrayOutOfBounds-Exception. I fixed that in revision 1098369.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
